    <insight>
    <p>
        In a geometric sequence, each term is obtained by multiplying the previous term by a constant ratio. When finding the sum, multiplying the entire sum by this ratio allows most terms to cancel when subtracted.
    </p>
    <p>
        This leads to the formula:
    </p>
    <p>
        <md>
            <mrow number="yes"> S_n = \amp\; \frac{a(r^n - 1)}{r - 1} </mrow>
        </md>
    </p>
</insight>

    <!-- Add further instruction (not in a block) to develop ideas as needed -->

    <xi:include href="../lesson-plan-templates/example-intro.ptx" />

    <!-- Add at least 3 examples -->
     <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Find the sum of the first <m>9</m> terms of the geometric sequence given as <m>8,24,72, ...</m>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow>a \amp = \; 8 </mrow>
                    <mrow> r \amp = \; \frac{24}{8} = 3 </mrow>
                    <mrow> n \amp = \; 9 </mrow>
                    <mrow> S_n =  \amp\; \frac{a(r^n-1)}{r-1} </mrow>
                    <mrow>S_9 \amp = \; \frac{8(3^9 - 1)}{3-1} </mrow>
                    <mrow> \amp = \; \frac{8(19683-1)} {2}</mrow>
                    <mrow> \amp =\; 78728 </mrow>
                </md>
                
            </p>
        </solution>
     </example>
     <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                The sum of the first three terms of a geometric series is <m>26</m>. If the common ratio is <m>3</m>, find the sum of the first six terms.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow>S_3 = 26 \amp </mrow>
                    <mrow> r \amp = \; 3 </mrow>
                    <mrow>n \amp = \; 3 </mrow>
                    <mrow> S_n \amp = \frac{a(r^n-1)}{r-1} </mrow>
                    <mrow> \text{Substituting} \amp </mrow>
                    <mrow> 26 \amp = \; \frac{a(3^3 - 1)}{3-1} </mrow>
                    <mrow> a \amp = \; \frac{26 \times 2}{26} </mrow>
                    <mrow> \amp = \; 2 </mrow>
                    <mrow> S_6 \amp = \; \frac{2(3^6 - 1)}{3-1} </mrow>
                    <mrow> \amp = \; 728 </mrow>
                </md>
                
            </p>
        </solution>
     </example>
     <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                
            </p>
        </statement>
     </example>

